MUFG will also invest USD 6 billion in the purchase of convertible bonds at a conversion price of USD 31.25 and will ensure a return of 10%.
Morgan Stanley has specified that the global transaction would be based on an average price of $29 per share, which is below its current rate of 28%.
By 5 p.m., however, Morgan Stanley was down 6.79% to $23.07.
"This strategic alliance is an important opportunity to accelerate Morgan Stanley's transition into a bank holding company", explained John Mack, managing director of the US group.
Morgan Stanley adopted this new charter last week, which should allow it to differentiate its stock, but still bring it under the control of the Federal Reserve.
Its alliance with MUFG also confirms how the current financial crisis is forcing the biggest names on Wall Street to take a much more cautious approach than they did before.
